INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (192001, 'Consistency matters. You must learn that giving people a consistent high-quality product is of importance, like building trust across your brand. This build relational wealth - people want to know what they are about to step into and with whom.', 35055, 0), (192002, 'You don''t need a million dollar to start a business. You just need a simple idea to make Billions', 35056, 0), (192003, 'You can’t be happy at work every day. No matter how much you love your job, there are still going to be bad days. And that’s cool—it’s always OK to have a bad day at work.', 35051, 0), (192004, 'Life is not about receiving. It''s about giving, knowing that someone might learn, understand or grow that little bit from the experience.', 35057, 0), (192005, 'If some musicians put half as much effort in to the business side as they do their outer look and appearances, they could be twice as far.', 8380, 0), (192006, 'Most companies that win don''t have a unique strategy; quite the opposite, they are doing what everyone else is doing but have figured out how to execute better.', 35050, 0), (192007, 'The simple truth is that technology is still a poor substitute for human interaction.', 35050, 0), (192008, 'If you give customers a chance, they’ll communicate with you in many ways.', 35050, 0), (192009, 'Strive for balance in your life. You are the heart and soul of your business so take care of yourself.', 35058, 0), (192010, 'Just finished [Capitalist in North Korea]—fascinating! What an experience. Wow." —Justin Rohrlich, Emmy Award Winner, Head Writer, Minyanville''s World In Review', 35059, 0), (192011, 'Customers are speaking to you implicitly via their behavior, captured in the footprints they leave behind in your systems.', 35050, 0), (192012, 'Realize that employees and the customers both have to be engaged, at the same time, to move your business forward for sustainable success.', 35050, 0), (192013, 'The key to success for Sony, and to everything in business, science and technology for that matter, is never to follow the others.', 30038, 0), (192014, 'A decision is only as strong as the belief standing behind it', 25094, 0), (192015, 'Research on the human brain has shown it is predisposed to think in the terms of a story.36 This predisposition is continuously reinforced and strengthened throughout the life of your brain. Imaging studies have shown only a small, quarter-sized region of your brain lights up when someone tells you a series of facts. However, when someone tells you a story laced with those facts, or those facts in action, your entire brain lights up. Not only can you program your mind with a story — you can program someone else’s mind.', 25094, 0), (192016, 'It’s not about the content we are creating but how much content our customers are creating for us.', 35060, 0), (192017, 'Life is all about exploring yourself, discovering yourself and grooming yourself, then you will surely stop negative thinking.', 24893, 0), (192018, 'Unlearn your knowledge about what WAS working to understand what is working NOW', 35060, 0), (192019, 'Japanese universities have a chair system that is a fixed hierarchy. This has its merits when trying to work as a laboratory on one theme. But if you want to do original work you must start young, and young people are limited by the chair system. Even if students cannot become assistant professors at an early age they should be encouraged to do original work....Industry is more likely to put its research effort into its daily business. It is very difficult for it to become involved in pure chemistry. There is a need to encourage long-range research, even if we don''t know its goal and if its application is unknown.', 35061, 0), (192020, 'The PC principle is to always treat your employees exactly as you want them to treat your best customers.', 965, 0), (192021, 'The U.S. stock market was now a class system, rooted in speed, of haves and have-nots. The haves paid for nanoseconds; the have-nots had no idea that nanoseconds had value. The haves enjoyed a perfect view of the market; the have-nots never saw the market at all.', 11243, 0), (192022, 'Its easier to start a global business than a local one, make your business one where you can work from anywhere in the world', 35060, 0), (192023, 'In the midst of battle, you need something versatile to keep your focus', 25094, 0), (192024, 'Don''t deal bitterly with the enemy you see. Deal with the greater enemy that sent your enemy to you. If you focus on dealing with the "retailer", remember that the "producer" can employ more "retailers" and what that means is that your life business will redefine you as "dealer of enemies". Satan is behind the plot!', 3301, 0), (192025, 'Solamon Energy Corp (SSL), "The Company", is neither offering nor has offered any shares for sale to the general public IPO and has not engaged any agents to do so, as shares can only be traded through GXG Markets by authorized brokers. Potential investors cautioned against solicitation by any unauthorized brokers to purchase SSL:GXG (London) shares. Economic Frauds has been reported. No affiliation with unauthorized offshore broker activity Fisher Capital (FCM) fraud.', 35062, 0), (192026, 'Competition in business is a blessing, for without it, we wouldn''t be motivated to improve.', 10427, 0), (192027, 'It''s not about money or connections. It''s the willingness to outwork and outlearn everyone.', 35063, 0), (192028, 'Some of us are happy with our African hair, thank you very much. I don''t want some poor Indian girl''s hair. And I wish to God I could buy black hair products from black people for once. How we going to make it in this country if we don''t make our own business?', 825, 0), (192029, 'Real estate is the best investment on earth, however, when the music stops playing, which happens occasionally, don''t be the one left without a chair.', 34978, 0), (192030, 'Competition exists to choose who gets the prize when the prize can’t be shared.', 1964, 0), (192031, 'A good entrepreneur is a good teacher.', 35064, 0), (192032, 'Don''t make up problems you don''t have yet. It''s not a problem until it''s a real problem. Most of the things you worry about never happen anyway.The decisions you make today don''t need to last forever. If circumstances change, your decisions CAN change. Decisions are temporary.Pay attention to today and worry about later when it gets here. Otherwise, you''ll waste energy, time and money fixating on problems that may never materialize."~ An excerpt from the awesome book, "Rework', 1929, 0), (192033, 'Every day is a training day and every event is a training event.', 35065, 0), (192034, 'Those who do not study their businesses do not stay in business.', 7677, 0), (192035, 'If you want to sustain excellence over a long time, you''d better come up with a system that works well. Anyone can sprint for a little while, but you can''t sprint for forty years.', 35066, 0), (192036, 'A title from the1966 movie"The Russians Are Coming,The Russians Are Coming," gives a new meaning toa phrase: "wait a minute, we''ve seen this movie before', 34978, 0), (192037, 'It''s not what you do, but what you appear to do.', 35065, 0), (192038, 'The minute you stop caring about your business, is the same minute your business stops caring about you.', 34978, 0), (192039, 'business is a part of my life,business is my stairway to heaven, I will be the successful businessman', 35067, 0), (192040, 'No Matter What, When, Where or Who … He is Forever My Daddy ~ MJ', 35068, 0), (192041, 'I started the business with a simple question: How can we make the process of buying a computer better? The answer was: Sell computers directly to the end customer. Eliminate the reseller''s markup and pass those savings on to the customer.', 35066, 0), (192042, 'Sometimes it''s better not to ask-or to listen-when tell you something can''t be done. I didn''t ask for per