eone else’s life. Don’t be trapped by dogma — which is living with the results of other people’s thinking. Don’t let the noise of others’ opinions drown out your own inner voice. And most important, have the courage to follow your heart and intuition. They somehow already know what you truly want to become. Everything else is secondary.', 1064, 0), (192188, 'We need a moderately-priced stock market… The market, like the Lord, helps those who help themselves. But, unlike the Lord, the market does not forgive those who know not what they do. For the investor, a too-high purchase price for the stock of an excellent company can undo the effects of a subsequent decade of favorable business developments.', 6410, 0), (192189, '...while extraordinary products and unique services still afford a competitive advantage, the one advantage that stands the test of time...is people.', 35091, 0), (192190, 'Service is not something you do. It is something you are.', 26454, 0), (192191, 'In business, if you want to make money, you have to spend money. If you want to have a result, you have to make an investment.', 173, 0), (192192, 'Are engineers better at business than business people? It’s debatable. Business people certainly seems to have bigger houses, drive fancier cars, wear nicer clothes and have better looking mates. Engineers lack the time management skills to spend that kind of money. They waste all their time inventing ways to make the most money in the quickest, most efficient way possible. And then when they figure it out, they optimize the process.', 35092, 0), (192193, 'People leave companies for two reasons. One, they don''t feel appreciated. And two, they don''t get along with their boss.', 19636, 0), (192194, 'Your money habits and investment strategy is not all about what you do, but much about who you are. Become the person it takes to do, succeed, and innovate.', 23233, 0), (192195, 'Lesson learned - in doing business, do not COMPETE but be COMPETITIVE.', 35093, 0